 Minigun

  - Tracer Rounds: Prioritizes fast enemies; +20% damage to fast raiders.
  - Suppressive Fire: Consecutive hits apply a stacking slow.
  - Ricochet Belt: Bullets have a chance to bounce to one nearby raider.
  - Overclocked Motor: Fire rate ramps up while shooting the same target.
  - Hollow Point: Bonus damage to unshielded enemies, reduced shield damage.
  - Heat Sink: Every 20th shot fires instantly with no cooldown.

  Cannon

  - Cluster Shells: Main shell splits into smaller secondary blasts.
  - Concussive Payload: Explosions briefly slow raiders.
  - Siege Round: Bigger damage and splash, much slower reload.
  - Shrapnel Burst: Explosion sends fragments into nearby enemies.
  - Crater Maker: Leaves a temporary hazard zone after impact.
  - Flak Shells: Can target flying enemies, reduced ground damage.

  Raygun

  - Chain Beam: Beam jumps to nearby raiders for reduced damage.
  - Cryo Focus: Freeze lasts longer, lower damage.
  - Thermal Lance: No freeze, but ramps damage on the same target.
  - Phase Beam: Ignores a portion of shields.
  - Prism Splitter: Fires weaker beams at two targets.
  - Stasis Lock: Rare chance to fully stop one enemy briefly.

  Anti-Air

  - Proximity Fuse: Missile explodes near flying targets for splash.
  - Lock-On Array: Faster missile travel and better cooldown.
  - Interceptor Battery: Fires multiple smaller missiles.
  - Sky Mine: Deploys delayed aerial mines along the flight path.
  - Ground Radar: Can hit ground units at reduced damage.
  - EMP Warhead: Extra shield damage and briefly slows flying enemies.

  Factory

  - Overtime Shift: Generates more resources while a wave is active.
  - Emergency Reserves: Instantly grants resources when health drops below a threshold.
  - Assembly Line: Reduces nearby tower upgrade costs.
  - Recycling Plant: Increases recycle value of nearby towers.
  - Power Grid: Nearby towers gain attack speed.
  - Ammo Depot: Nearby cannon/minigun towers gain damage.

  Missile / Launcher-style tower
  If missile becomes its own tower later:

  - Swarm Rockets: Fires several low-damage rockets.
  - Thermobaric Payload: Larger explosion, lower direct damage.
  - Guidance Chip: Retargets if the original target dies.
  - Bunker Buster: Huge shield/armor damage.
  - Napalm Trail: Leaves a burning path.
  - Split Warhead: Missile separates into smaller impacts near the target.

  Universal Research
  These could apply to any tower type, but I’d use them sparingly:

  - Extended Optics: +15% range.
  - Rapid Servos: +10% attack speed.
  - Capacitor Core: +20% shield damage.
  - Efficiency Tuning: -15% upgrade cost.
  - Targeting AI: Unlocks smarter priority modes.
  - Veteran Crew: Tower gains a small bonus after enough kills.